.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::HttpAuth \- NIP\-98 HTTP auth
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 4
\&    use Net::Nostr::HttpAuth qw(
\&        create_auth_event create_auth_header
\&        parse_auth_header validate_auth_event
\&    );
\&
\&    # Client: create an Authorization header for a GET request
\&    my $header = create_auth_header(
\&        key    => $key,
\&        url    => \*(Aqhttps://api.example.com/data\*(Aq,
\&        method => \*(AqGET\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # "Nostr eyJpZCI6Ii..."
\&
\&    # Client: POST with payload hash
\&    my $body = \*(Aq{"name":"test"}\*(Aq;
\&    my $header = create_auth_header(
\&        key     => $key,
\&        url     => \*(Aqhttps://api.example.com/upload\*(Aq,
\&        method  => \*(AqPOST\*(Aq,
\&        payload => $body,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Server: parse and validate
\&    my $event = parse_auth_header($header);
\&    validate_auth_event($event,
\&        url    => \*(Aqhttps://api.example.com/data\*(Aq,
\&        method => \*(AqGET\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-98 HTTP auth. Uses kind 27235 ephemeral nostr events
to authorize HTTP requests. The client signs an event containing the
request URL and method, base64\-encodes it, and sends it in the
\&\f(CW\*(C`Authorization\*(C'\fR HTTP header with the \f(CW\*(C`Nostr\*(C'\fR scheme. The server
decodes the event and validates the kind, timestamp, URL, and method.
.PP
When the request has a body (POST, PUT, PATCH), the client SHOULD
include a \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR tag containing the SHA\-256 hex hash of the body.
The server MAY check this tag to verify the body is authorized.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.IX Header "FUNCTIONS"
All functions are exportable. None are exported by default.
.SS create_auth_event
.IX Subsection "create_auth_event"
.Vb 7
\&    my $event = create_auth_event(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        url        => $absolute_url,
\&        method     => $http_method,
\&        payload    => $body,        # optional
\&        created_at => time(),       # optional, defaults to now
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 27235 Net::Nostr::Event with \f(CW\*(C`u\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR
tags. If \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR is provided, adds a \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR tag with the
SHA\-256 hex hash of the body. The event content is always empty.
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR is missing. Croaks if
\&\f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is not 64\-character lowercase hex.
.PP
The returned event is unsigned. Use "sign_event" in Net::Nostr::Key
to sign it before encoding.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $event = create_auth_event(
\&        pubkey => \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32,
\&        url    => \*(Aqhttps://api.example.com/data\*(Aq,
\&        method => \*(AqGET\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.SS create_auth_header
.IX Subsection "create_auth_header"
.Vb 7
\&    my $header = create_auth_header(
\&        key        => $nostr_key,
\&        url        => $absolute_url,
\&        method     => $http_method,
\&        payload    => $body,           # optional
\&        created_at => time(),          # optional, defaults to now
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates, signs, and base64\-encodes a kind 27235 event, returning
a complete \f(CW\*(C`Authorization\*(C'\fR header value in the format
\&\f(CW\*(C`Nostr <base64>\*(C'\fR. The \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR must be a Net::Nostr::Key
object with a private key for signing. Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`key\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR,
or \f(CW\*(C`method\*(C'\fR is missing.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $header = create_auth_header(
\&        key    => $key,
\&        url    => \*(Aqhttps://api.example.com/data\*(Aq,
\&        method => \*(AqGET\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&    # "Nostr eyJpZCI6Ii..."
.Ve
.SS parse_auth_header
.IX Subsection "parse_auth_header"
.Vb 1
\&    my $event = parse_auth_header($header_value);
.Ve
.PP
Parses an \f(CW\*(C`Authorization\*(C'\fR header value. Validates the \f(CW\*(C`Nostr\*(C'\fR
scheme, decodes the base64 payload, and parses the JSON into a
Net::Nostr::Event using "from_wire" in Net::Nostr::Event.
Croaks if the header is missing, uses the wrong scheme, or
contains invalid base64 or JSON.
.PP
.Vb 1
\&    my $event = parse_auth_header(\*(AqNostr eyJpZCI6Ii...\*(Aq);
.Ve
.SS validate_auth_event
.IX Subsection "validate_auth_event"
.Vb 6
\&    validate_auth_event($event,
\&        url         => $absolute_url,
\&        method      => $http_method,
\&        payload     => $body,         # optional
\&        time_window => 60,            # optional, seconds, default 60
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Performs the server\-side validation checks specified by NIP\-98:
.IP "0. The event ID and Schnorr signature are cryptographically verified via ""validate"" in Net::Nostr::Event. This ensures the event was actually signed by the claimed pubkey and has not been tampered with." 4
.IX Item "0. The event ID and Schnorr signature are cryptographically verified via ""validate"" in Net::Nostr::Event. This ensures the event was actually signed by the claimed pubkey and has not been tampered with."
.PD 0
.ie n .IP "1. The ""kind"" MUST be 27235." 4
.el .IP "1. The \f(CWkind\fR MUST be \f(CW27235\fR." 4
.IX Item "1. The kind MUST be 27235."
.ie n .IP "2. The ""created_at"" timestamp MUST be within ""time_window"" seconds of the current time (default 60 seconds)." 4
.el .IP "2. The \f(CWcreated_at\fR timestamp MUST be within \f(CWtime_window\fR seconds of the current time (default 60 seconds)." 4
.IX Item "2. The created_at timestamp MUST be within time_window seconds of the current time (default 60 seconds)."
.ie n .IP "3. The ""u"" tag MUST exactly match the request URL (including query parameters)." 4
.el .IP "3. The \f(CWu\fR tag MUST exactly match the request URL (including query parameters)." 4
.IX Item "3. The u tag MUST exactly match the request URL (including query parameters)."
.ie n .IP "4. The ""method"" tag MUST match the HTTP method used." 4
.el .IP "4. The \f(CWmethod\fR tag MUST match the HTTP method used." 4
.IX Item "4. The method tag MUST match the HTTP method used."
.PD
.PP
If \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR is provided and the event has a \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR tag, the
tag value is checked against the SHA\-256 hex hash of the body. If
the server does not provide \f(CW\*(C`payload\*(C'\fR, the tag is not checked.
.PP
Returns 1 on success. Croaks with a descriptive message on failure.
Servers SHOULD respond with HTTP 401 when validation fails.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    eval { validate_auth_event($event, url => $url, method => \*(AqGET\*(Aq) };
\&    if ($@) {
\&        # respond with 401 Unauthorized
\&    }
.Ve
